name: Limited-Use Whump the Giant Finisher
description: Whump the giant delivers a smashing finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Limited-Use Spectre Finisher
description: A shadowy assassin deals the fatal blow with this finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Limited-Use Sanctified Finisher
description: Send your opponents to the afterlife with this spirit-infused finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Limited-Use Thornroot Finisher
description: Use your opponent as fertilizer for this lethal finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Limited-Use Grave Finisher
description: Send your opponents to their grave, literally, with this tombstone finisher in PvP and WvW.

name: Limited-Use Super Explosive Finisher
description: Blast your opponents with this Super Adventure Box Super Bomb finishing move in PvP and WvW.

name: Preserved Red Iris Flower
description: <c=@flavor>Lovingly preserved specimen of an exceedingly rare iris.</c>

description: <c=@flavor>Smuggled out of Cantha long ago, a relic of the Great House of Lutgardis.</c>

name: Warmaster's Family Heirloom
description: <c=@flavor>Generations of norn-etched runes cover this dolyak horn. The most recent is a symbol of the Vigil.</c>

name: Totem of the Gorilla
description: <c=@flavor>An intrepid norn artist paid respect to a far-flung Spirit of the Wild with this carving.</c>

name: Fledgling Charm
description: <c=@flavor>Young tengu are given charms like this for protection.</c>

name: Anton's Secret
description: <c=@flavor>An item to be hidden in the most unlikely of places.</c>

name: Passiflora Karkinata
description: <c=@flavor>An extremely rare and powerful floral specimen.</c>

name: Ancient Karka Carapace
description: <c=@flavor>Part of the ancient karka that attacked Lion's Arch. Mysterious magics seem to be woven into its chitinous shell.</c>

name: Molten Ore
description: <c=@flavor>A dark artifact of the combined forces of the Flame Legion and dredge. This ore seems too impure to properly refine, but it gleams with dark potential.</c>

name: Big Mama's Tooth
description: <c=@flavor>Legends speak of "Big Mama," the largest drake broodmother that ever lived. If she still does, it seems she's short at least one tooth.</c>

name: Amulet of Protection
description: <c=@flavor>Stolen from the body of a long-forgotten lord during the Guild Wars.</c>

name: Salma's Diamond Jubilee Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>Queen Salma's reign was long and prosperous. Such prosperity has long been missed in Kryta.<c>

name: Kodan Prayer Beads
description: <c=@flavor>A string of 49 ivory beads.</c>

name: Amulet of the Skies
description: <c=@flavor>A talented Durmand Priory scholar based this necklace on ancient astrological charts found on jotun megaliths.</c>

name: Petrified Skull Juju
description: <c=@flavor>An ancient relic of the mystic beings of Echovald Forest.</c>

name: Nornbear's Remembrance
description: <c=@flavor>Once a painful reminder to Jora of her brother's curse.</c>

name: Archaic Grawl Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>From a time before the grawl had a spoken language.</c>

name: The Southsun Rose
description: <c=@flavor>The largest pink diamond in all of Tyria.</c>

name: Charisma
description: <c=@flavor>The locket contains a picture of Kolijn Johansson, Trade Administrator of Hoelbrak.</c>

name: Third-Place Medal
description: <c=@flavor>Congratulations from the Divinity's Reach Fancy Cat Association! Everyone is fancy in their own way.</c>

name: Prayer to Otter
description: <c=@flavor>Otter is a fickle spirit, but when she does grant a boon, it is a powerful gift indeed.</c>

name: The Queen's Necklace
description: <c=@flavor>Commissioned for Queen Jennah by a council member, but found too ornate for her tastes.</c>

name: Luxon Pendant
description: <c=@flavor>Smuggled out of Cantha long ago, a relic of the Serpent Clan.<c>

name: The Beetlestone Diamond
description: <c=@flavor>Mined from the Onyx Fields of Southsun Cove for the pleasure of Lord Beetlestone.</c>

name: Protomatter Chain
description: <c=@flavor>Some strange, ethereal material from the Mists has solidified into this odd necklace.</c>

name: Guild Commendation
description: Earned for completing guild missions. Can be traded to Tyrian Explorer Olread in Lion's Arch for rewards.

name: Guild Armor Station
description: Spawns field crafting stations for armorsmith, leatherworker, tailor, and jeweler. Lasts for 1 hour.

name: Guild Experience Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% experience from kills for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other experience banners.

name: Guild Gathering Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% gathering chance for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other gathering banners.

name: Guild Karma Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% karma boost for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other karma banners.

name: Guild Magic Find Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% boost to magic find for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other magic find banners.

name: Guild Road Marker
description: Summons a guild banner that will apply swiftness to any ally who touches it.

name: Guild Banquet
description: Spawns a banquet table, keg and various other party items which players can eat and drink from. Lasts 1 hour.

name: Summon Guild Vault
description: Summons the guild vault to your location for easy access. Must have vault permissions.

name: Guild Weapon Stations
description: Spawns field crafting stations for weaponsmith, huntsman, artificer, and chef. Lasts for 1 hour.

name: Guild Heroes Banner
description: Spawns a guild banner that will give +15% karma, +15% magic find, +15% experience from kills, +15% gold from kills, +15% increased movement speed, and +15% gathering chance to any ally that touches it for 30 minutes. Does not stack with other banner boosts.

name: Guild Gathering and Swiftness Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% gathering chance and 15% movement speed boost for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other gathering or speed banners.

name: Guild Gold and Magic Find Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% boost to gold from kills and +15% boost to magic find for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other gold or magic find banners.

name: Guild Gold Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% boost to gold from kills for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other gold banners.

name: Guild Karma and Experience Banner
description: Summons a guild banner that will give +15% karma and +15% experience from kills for 30 minutes to any ally who touches it. Does not stack with other karma or experience banners.

name: Endless Guild Banner Tonic
description: Transform into your guild's banner for 15 minutes or until hit. You cannot move while transformed.

name: Mini Red Siege Golem
description: Double-click to summon this mini to follow you around. Only one mini may be in use at a time.

name: Mini Green Siege Golem
description: Double-click to summon this mini to follow you around. Only one mini may be in use at a time.

name: Mini Blue Siege Golem
description: Double-click to summon this mini to follow you around. Only one mini may be in use at a time.

name: Arrow Cart Blueprint
description: Use to construct an arrow cart build site. The arrow cart's primary function is to deal moderate area damage to infantry. Range 2,500. Requires 25 supply to complete.

name: Trebuchet Blueprint
description: Use to construct a trebuchet build site. The trebuchet's primary function is to deal heavy area damage to walls or moderate damage to gates. Range 10,000. Requires 50 supply to complete.

name: Refugee's Sword Belt
description: This sturdy sword belt has notches carved into its leather to track kills. A refugee in the Black Citadel might want it back.

name: Refugee's Logbook
description: This weathered logbook details the endeavors and demise of an Iron Legion warband. A refugee in the Black Citadel might want it back.

name: Refugee's Ship in a Bottle
description: A handcrafted ship within a surprisingly spotless bottle. Etched into the boat's side is a tribute to the Spirits of the Wild. A refugee in Hoelbrak might want this back.

name: Refugee's Compass
description: Silhouettes of the four Spirits of the Wild are masterfully carved into this compass's lid. A refugee in Hoelbrak might want it back.

name: Refugee's Goblet
description: This enormous goblet, stained with countless shades of ale, belongs to a refugee in Hoelbrak. They might want it back.

name: Refugee's Wooden Soldier
description: This wooden toy, crafted to resemble Toymaker Tixx's Wintersday soldiers, looks well-loved. A refugee in the Black Citadel might want it back.
